<div id="review_1350318782" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1350318782" />
    <a title="Josh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5366206-josh"><img alt="Josh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1445467353p2/5366206.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1350318782?book_show_action=true">Feb 05, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Josh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Josh" href="/user/show/5366206-josh">Josh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1350318782" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11106238923924544650">It’s tough to review a book that was never finished and meant to be destroyed. How much of this novel would have been edited out? What would have been added to make it whole? <br/><br/>I did not enjoy this unfinished manuscript. I love Kafka and I’d hoped to grow my love of his writing here, but nothing grows inside the castle except for discontent, it would seem.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


