<span id="freeTextContainer18095821800997618294">I found this book very frustrating and difficult to get through, yet at the same time enjoyed the actual story and found some parallels with the village and our world today.<br/>Two things that I found particularly frustrating:<br/>The use of K. as his name and the constant use of it with the full stop really disrupted my reading flow. Also it must be the most printed name in book history which didn&apos;t help.<br/>The long rambling diatribes politicking over minute details. Whole I understood this as part of the </span>
  <span id="freeText18095821800997618294" style="display:none">I found this book very frustrating and difficult to get through, yet at the same time enjoyed the actual story and found some parallels with the village and our world today.<br />Two things that I found particularly frustrating:<br />The use of K. as his name and the constant use of it with the full stop really disrupted my reading flow. Also it must be the most printed name in book history which didn't help.<br />The long rambling diatribes politicking over minute details. Whole I understood this as part of the overall picture of ultra bureaucracy it went way too far in places, such as in the section with the new bar girl.</span>
