      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Geoffrey" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Geoffrey" href="/user/show/5252442-geoffrey">Geoffrey</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer515532039" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10686072348585401278">As a government employee, I found this infuriatingly familiar. Kafka perfectly encapsulated what bureaucracy feels like from the inside. Truth be told, I did not finish it. I just assumed he dies without finishing the quest, an ending for which there was much foreshadowing. The repetition was so familiar from my own life, I couldn&apos;t continue on, lest I forget what was real and what was the book.</span>
  <span id="freeText10686072348585401278" style="display:none">As a government employee, I found this infuriatingly familiar. Kafka perfectly encapsulated what bureaucracy feels like from the inside. Truth be told, I did not finish it. I just assumed he dies without finishing the quest, an ending for which there was much foreshadowing. The repetition was so familiar from my own life, I couldn't continue on, lest I forget what was real and what was the book.</span>
